<header>
<a href="/blog/2016/07/29/spring-cloud-data-flow-for-apache-yarn-1-0-1-released"><h2 class="member-post--title">Spring Cloud Data Flow for Apache YARN 1.0.1 released</h2></a>
<div class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon releases"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/releases">Releases</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2016-07-29 08:08:31.727">July 29, 2016</time>
</div>
</div>
</header>
<section class="member-post--summary"><p>We are pleased to announce the release of <a href="https://cloud.spring.io/spring-cloud-dataflow-server-yarn">Spring Cloud Data Flow for Apache YARN</a> 1.0.1.RELEASE. </p>
<p>Spring Cloud Data Flow for Apache YARN provides support for orchestrating long-running (streaming) and short-lived (task/batch) data microservices on Apache YARN.</p>
<p>Apart from usual minor fixes, we have worked on the following themes.</p>
<ul>
<li>Support for kerberos and integration to automated ambari kerberos setup.</li>
<li>Support for HDFS HA Namenode setup.</li>
<li>New extension to <code>dataflow-shell</code> adding <code>hadoop fs</code> basic commands.</li>
</ul>
<p>For a complete list of changes and improvements, please refer to<br><a href="https://github.com/spring-cloud/spring-cloud-dataflow-server-yarn/issues?q=milestone%3A1.0.1.RELEASE+is%3Aclosed">1.0.1.RELEASE server release</a>, <a href="https://github.com/spring-cloud/spring-cloud-deployer-yarn/issues?q=milestone%3A1.0.1.RELEASE+is%3Aclosed">1.0.1.RELEASE deployer release</a>, <a href="https://github.com/spring-cloud/spring-cloud-dataflow-rpm/issues?q=milestone%3A1.0-2-RELEASE%20is%3Aclosed%20">1.0-2.RELEASE rpm release</a> and <a href="https://github.com/spring-cloud/spring-cloud-dataflow-ambari-rpm/issues?q=milestone%3A1.0-2-RELEASE%20is%3Aclosed%20">1.0-2.RELEASE ambari plugin release</a>.</p>
</section>
